"Introduction to Banking and Climate Change (Possible Planet)"

=Description=

"This compilation video presents a collection of statements that relate to the potential of money to solve social and environmental problems. The compilation covers the supply of money, the role of commercial banks, the role of central banks, the central bank response to climate change, and the emergence of Central Bank Digital Currencies (CBDC). This compilation does not set out to explain the issues in detail, but it reveals that there is an  emerging narrative that connects central bank mandates to the problem of climate change. The video compilation also hints at the idea that CBDC's provide an opportunity to develop new public policies."

